        </p>
        <ul class="explain">
          <li>
            <em>Load</em>: Divide the load in pounds by 10 and and
            subtract strength.  If this exceeds zero, subtract this
            from any physical or combat skill.
          </li>
          <li>
            <em>Piety</em>: Serves as skill for specific magic/religious
            rituals.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <h4 id="piety">Piety</h4>
        <ul class="explain">
          <li>
            <b>Level 0:</b> NN knows that the reigion exist but cannot
            separate it from other convocations.
          </li>
          <li>
            <b>Level 5:</b> Lip service payed to the religion and ability
            to separate it from other major faiths.
          </li>
          <li>
            <b>Level 10:</b> The main tenants of the religion are known
            and followed on individual level. Sects or heresies are not
            considered.
          </li>
          <li>
            <b>Level 15:</b> The religion is quoted often and other faiths
            routinely treated underhanded. Proselytizing is rarely attempted.
          </li>
          <li>
            <b>Level 20:</b> At this level the adherent is actively seeking
            to further the tenants of the religion outside of his immediate
            domain. Distinction between inner-religion minutiae are important.
          </li>
          <li>
            <b>Level 25:</b> Heresy is abhorred more than other religions.
            Support for the religion takes precendents over other interests
            almost always.
          </li>
          <li>
            <b>Level 30:</b> The adherent is a prophet for the religion and
            accepts otherwise serious consequences for following details of
            his faith. May invent rituals and the like.
          </li>
        </ul>
