        <h3 id="weapons">Weapons/Armour</h3>
        <p>
          The A/D numbers are used as
          additional modifiers (divided by five) when the weapon is
          used in accord with its fighting style. Using a weapon or a
          combination in the wrong hand implies a penalty of-<n2/>.
        </p>
        <p>
          The weapon and armour B/E/P values are each subtracted, the
          result added to the injury dimension. All appropriate dimensions
          apply for recovery.
        </p>
        <h3 id="armour">Impediments</h3>
        <p>
          All impediments affect all types of activity.  All are
          modified by Stamina(live)/Quality(dead).  Recovery is 
          only possible during rest.  Dead objects do not recover
          but are repaired. Edge/Point may infect. Chance per day
          is penalty being healed as percentage.
        </p>
        <p>
          Impediments below add HR penalty as max component.
          HR as percentage is rolled once per unit time for +1 % or -1 % in HR.
          For diesase and infection this unit is one day.
        </p>
